content_vision: I don't want to hear what you think I want. I got angry myself when I was in your position before. But now that I don't get mad when I do this, I just don't understand you. What am I to give credit: praise or thanks?
text:
Intro:
They said I couldn't do it, but now they're just jealous,
you were my inspiration, my drive, my fuel.

Chorus:
We're diamonds in the rough, but we shine so bright,
they can't dim our light
So don't you let them dim our shine,
we'll rise above every time.

Verse 1:
They say I'm living a life of lies,
but I'm just breaking free, no longer bound by ties.
I used to walk on eggshells, afraid to speak my mind,
but now I'm breaking free, leaving all the doubts behind.
They said I couldn't do it, but I proved them all wrong, now I'm rising up like a phoenix,
singing my own empowering song.
I used to wear a mask, afraid to show who I am, but now I'm shedding all my layers,
and finally taking a stand.

Pre-Chorus 1:
I used to sit in silence, afraid to speak my mind, but
now I've found my voice and I'm leaving all the doubts behind.

Verse 2:
I used to chase after validation, seeking approval in everything I'd do, but now I've found my worth within myself,
and I don't need anyone to tell me the truth.
I used to chase after shadows, always searching for something more,
but now I've found my peace within, and I don't need to keep score.
Every step I take, I feel a weight lifting off my chest,
no longer shackled by your opinions, I can finally rest.
But now I see through your facade, all the lies and the deceit,
I've broken free from your hold, and I won't accept defeat.

Pre-Chorus 2:
With every breath I take, I feel a newfound strength, no longer held down by your chains,
I've finally found my worth, and I won't be tamed.

Bridge:
I don't need their validation, I found my own worth,
and with you by my side, I'll conquer the earth.
With you by my side, I'll conquer the world;
your love is the only thing that makes me whole.

Intro:
Welcome to the story of my life,
full of ups and downs, battles and strife.
It's a journey of self-discovery,
filled with laughter, tears, and sometimes misery.

Chorus:
I rise above the hate and drama, take control of my fate,
no longer a bystander.
But I keep pushing through, chasing my dreams,
ignoring the critics and their destructive schemes.

Verse 1:
But I won't let your words bring me down, I'll keep my head held high,
showing the world that I'm not afraid to try.
I used to let your words cut me deep, but now
I've found my strength and I'm not afraid to speak.
You used to judge me, now you're begging for my attention,

Pre-Chorus 1:

Bridge:
I used to be blinded by your words, but now I see the light,

But I won't let your hate consume me, I'll rise above and break free,

Intro:

Chorus:
I used to care, but now I see
the only validation I need is from me.
But now I've found my own path, my own way to be free,
I don't need your approval, I'll just be me.

Verse 1:
I used to chase after acceptance, but now I see
That all I ever needed was already inside me
I used to think fitting in was the key, but now I know,
being true to myself is what sets me free.
I used to think I needed your approval, your validation,
But now I see, it was all just a manipulation.
But now I've let go of that anger, found peace within myself,
understanding that your words hold no power, they're just an empty shelf.

Pre-Chorus 1:
I used to play a role, just to please the crowd,
but now I've found my own voice, and the applause is loud.

Verse 2:
I used to crave attention, but now I see, that I was just
seeking love and validation from those who couldn't truly love me.
Now I see that love and acceptance start from within,
and my heart is full, no need for outside validation.
But now I see, your judgments don't define me,
I'll live my life on my own terms and be happy.
Now I see that the love and acceptance I sought from you, was just a hollow facade,
and I took back my power and raised my middle finger to your facade.

Pre-Chorus 2:
But now I see, I don't need your validation or approval,
I've found my own inner strength, my own self-love ritual.

Bridge:
I used to play by your rules, but now I see,
there's no limit to what I can be.
I used to play their game, trying to fit in,
but now I see, the only game I need to win is within.

Intro:
Welcome to my world, where the grind never stops
Success is the only option, failure's not in my thoughts.

Chorus:
Got my mind on my money, ain't got no time for games
I'll keep climbing to the top, no matter what they sayin'
When I was down, you kicked me while I was on the ground
But now I'm on top, and you wanna come around

Verse 1:

They used to laugh at my dreams, called them foolish and naive,

I've got my sights set on greatness, and I won't stop until I find,

Pre-Chorus 1:
Now I'm flying high,
leaving all the haters behind

Verse 2:
I used to let the doubts get in my head, but

I spread my wings and soar towards my dreams
But I rose above the doubts, took control of my fate,
now my success speaks for itself, and they can't debate.
But now that I've shed my insecurities,
I've found my true self and my opportunities.

Pre-Chorus 2:
I'll never let anyone dim my light,

Bridge:
Just when I thought I knew it all, you
came along and showed me there's more to explore
I used to hold back,
afraid to be true,

Intro:
I'm not asking for validation, or seeking anyone's approval,

Chorus:

My past may have been rough,
but it led me to where I am today

But I'll rise above it all and show you my real deal

need validation from you anymore
